# Implementation Plan: ControlIA v2.0 (VoltAgent Edition)

This plan outlines the complete technical evolution of the ControlIA SaaS platform into an autonomous, voice-first agentic system using the **Agent Swarm (PARL)** architecture.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Paradigm Shift:** The system is moving from a traditional command-driven bot (`/vender`, `/cliente`) to a natural language "Zero Friction" interface. This requires a robust orchestration layer.

> [!WARNING]
> **API Keys Required:** To execute this plan, we will need:
> 1. `MOONSHOT_API_KEY` (for Kimi K2.5).
> 2. `OPENAI_API_KEY` (for Whisper transcription, if Kimi K2.5 doesn't handle OGG/Voice directly).
> 3. `MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN` (for VROOM-based routing).

> [!CAUTION]
> **Database Transition:** We will introduce **Prisma ORM** in the TypeScript service. The Python bot will coexist with its `psycopg` pool, so we must ensure schema changes are synchronized manually until a full migration occurs.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Orchestration Layer (`core-agent`)
A Node.js microservice built with **VoltAgent** that acts as the "Brain".

#### [NEW] `core-agent/` (Node.js/TypeScript)
- **Framework:** [VoltAgent](https://github.com/voltagent/voltagent)
- **Model:** **Kimi K2.5** (Multimodal MoE)
- **Architecture:** Agent Swarm (PARL)
    - **Orchestrator Agent:** Decomposes user intent.
    - **Financial Agent:** Skill `registrar_pago`, `consultar_cartera`.
    - **Inventory Agent:** Skill `descontar_stock`, `consultar_precios`.
    - **Context Agent (RAG):** Skill `consultar_preferencias` (Semantic Memory).

#### [NEW] `core-agent/prisma/schema.prisma`
- Mirror the existing PostgreSQL schema.
- Add `vector` column to `clientes` or a new `contex_memory` table for RAG.

### 2. Capabilities Engine: VoltAgent Skills

#### [NEW] `core-agent/src/skills/`
- **Skill CRM:** Autonomous lookup and note registration.
- **Skill Sales:** Handle complex orders from text/voice.
- **Skill Logistics:** Integrate **VROOM** for dynamic routing.
- **Skill Vision:** Multimodal processing for photo-based audits.

### 3. Telegram Interface (Python Bot) [MODIFY]

#### [MODIFY] `bot.py`
- Add `voice_handler` to capture `.ogg` messages from Telegram.
- Add `photo_handler` for vision-based audits.
- Implement a "Talk to Agent" mode that sends all non-command text to `core-agent`.

#### [MODIFY] `routing_engine.py`
- Transition from static `scikit-learn` clusters to dynamic **VROOM** optimization.

## Open Questions

